# Context Pilot — Caddy reverse proxy + private-CA TLS (tls internal).
#
# "Tout local, rien sur le web": this box has NO public DNS and NO public ACME.
# Caddy terminates all TLS with its built-in CA (`tls internal`); the root is
# distributed to clients out-of-band from the IT section of cockpit Settings.
#
# IMPORTANT: this file is a BOOTSTRAP fallback only. The orchestrator REGENERATES
# it at boot and on every identity change — rendering explicit name/IP site
# addresses, the cockpit on :443 once provisioned, and the :80→:443 redirect
# (see crates/cp-orchestrator/src/transport/it/caddy.rs). The orchestrator starts
# before Caddy (the caddy.service unit has After=context-pilot.service), so by the
# time Caddy reads this it has usually been replaced. Until then we serve the
# cockpit over cleartext :80 for the day-0 flow (design §13.4 — no :9090 plane).
{
	# LAN appliance: private CA only, never reach out to public ACME.
	auto_https disable_redirects
}

# Day-0 cockpit — cleartext :80 until the box is provisioned. An IT operator logs
# in here, changes the seeded password, and names the box; that provisions it and
# brings the private-CA :443 cockpit up (the orchestrator then regenerates this
# file so :80 becomes a redirect to :443).
:80 {
	reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:7878
}

# The product cockpit (:443) and the :80→:443 redirect are intentionally ABSENT
# here: an unprovisioned box has no cert yet. The orchestrator adds those blocks
# only after the box is named (provisioned).
